Being a Strength and Sports Performance Coach isn’t just about getting my athletes stronger but getting them ready for what’s next. This isn’t  just a job or a hobby but an eat, sleep and breathe lifestyle of mine. I get athletes in and teach them how to properly lift, and get them faster and stronger. Then when they decide on a school, I make sure if they want to pursue sports to get in touch with their next s&c coach and get a plan of attack ready for them so when they show up they are more than ready to perform at the next level. 
💪💪💪💪

“Lead From The Front” is a common saying I tell my athletes day in and day out. I train as hard as I can to show them. Anything I do in this world is 110% if not more and it’s because I want show them not just tell them. Here is a picture of Big Owen 319lb 6’9 attempting a new hang clean PR of 225lb.
I’m 5’8 245lb and if he fails and go backwards there is a high chance of my ass going through a wall but “Lead from the Front“ and show no fear nor no doubt! As a coach you must never show any doubt in an athlete no matter how crazy it could look. They follow your lead. Big Owen failed this lift but still hit a new PR of 215. We’ve come a long way and we will continue to go as he gets ready to set sail to Fordham soon. My job is never done continuing to get him ready not just physically but mentally.

#mondaymotivation
